## Pagination

### Offset Pagination (Simple Lists)

```python
stmt = (
    select(Product)
    .where(Product.status == "active", Product.deleted_at.is_(None))
    .order_by(Product.created_at.desc())
    .offset(offset)
    .limit(page_size)
)
```

Acceptable for admin UI with moderate datasets.

Avoid deep offsets (`OFFSET 100000`) on large tables — use keyset pagination.

### Keyset (Cursor) Pagination

```python
stmt = (
    select(Product)
    .where(
        Product.status == "active",
        Product.deleted_at.is_(None),
        Product.id < cursor_id,  # cursor from previous page
    )
    .order_by(Product.id.desc())
    .limit(page_size)
)
```

Required for:

- Product catalog infinite scroll at scale
- Order history for high-volume customers
- Admin exports

Return `next_cursor` in API response.

