## Filtering and Search

### Parameterized Queries Only

Always bind parameters — never interpolate user input:

```python
# CORRECT
stmt = select(Product).where(Product.slug == slug)

# WRONG — SQL injection
stmt = text(f"SELECT * FROM products WHERE slug = '{slug}'")
```

### Full-Text Search

```python
from sqlalchemy import func

search_vector = func.to_tsvector("english", Product.title + " " + func.coalesce(Product.description, ""))
search_query = func.plainto_tsquery("english", query)

stmt = select(Product).where(search_vector.op("@@")(search_query))
```

### JSONB Filters

```python
stmt = select(Product).where(Product.attributes["brand"].astext == brand)
```

Ensure GIN or expression index exists (`database/03-indexing`).

