## Query Performance Standards

| Metric | Target |
|--------|--------|
| API read queries (p95) | < 50ms |
| API write queries (p95) | < 100ms |
| Catalog listing (p95) | < 100ms |
| Admin reports | < 2s (with pagination) |

Investigate any query exceeding 500ms.

### EXPLAIN Workflow

```sql
EXPLAIN (ANALYZE, BUFFERS, FORMAT TEXT)
SELECT ...
```

Look for:

- Sequential scans on large tables → add index
- High `rows removed by filter` → index or rewrite query
- Nested loop with high row counts → join order or index
- Sort operations on large sets → index matching ORDER BY

---

## Read Replicas

Route to replica:

- Analytics dashboards
- Search indexing exports
- Historical report generation

Route to primary:

- All writes
- Read-after-write (order placed → order detail)
- Payment status checks
- Inventory availability during checkout

---

## Caching Interaction

Cache keys must include entity version or updated_at:

```
product:{id}:v{updated_at_timestamp}
```

Invalidate cache on write — do not rely on TTL alone for price/inventory.

PostgreSQL remains source of truth; cache is advisory for reads.

